businessUnit":"worldwide","cards":[{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[],"html":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\"http:\u002F\u002Fwww.bbc.com\u002Ffuture\u002Fstory\u002F20180521-the-health-gap-how-women-experience-the-medical-system\"\u003E\u003Cimg src=\"http:\u002F\u002Fichef.bbci.co.uk\u002Fimages\u002Fic\u002Fraw\u002Fp067ssc1.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"&ldquo;The\" width=\"100%\" \u002F\u003E\u003C\u002Fa\u003E\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIt all started with a Mexican yam.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIt was 1942 and a chemistry professor from Pennsylvania was looking for a cheap source of progesterone. The hormone had many uses at the time, including preventing miscarriages and treating women going through the menopause.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIn fact, Russell Marker already had invented a way to make progesterone from a chemical in certain plants. One option was the tubers of wild Japanese yams. But these were thin and weedy &ndash; they just didn&rsquo;t contain enough of the hormone.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cem\u003EYou might also like these other stories in the \u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Ca href=\"http:\u002F\u002Fwww.bbc.com\u002Ffuture\u002Fstory\u002F20180521-the-health-gap-how-women-experience-the-medical-system\" target=\"_blank\"\u003EHealth Gap\u003C\u002Fa\u003E:\u003Cbr \u002F\u003E\u003C\u002Fstrong\u003E\u003C\u002Fem\u003E&bull; \u003Ca href=\"http:\u002F\u002Fwww.bbc.com\u002Ffuture\u002Fstory\u002F20180717-the-pelvic-floor-is-still-a-mystery-in-anatomy\" target=\"_blank\"\u003EThe mystery of the pelvic floor\u003C\u002Fa\u003E\u003Cbr \u002F\u003E&bull; \u003Ca href=\"http:\u002F\u002Fwww.bbc.com\u002Ffuture\u002Fstory\u002F20180518-the-inequality-in-how-women-are-treated-for-pain\" target=\"_blank\"\u003EWhy are doctors dismissing women's pain?\u003C\u002Fa\u003E\u003Cbr \u002F\u003E&bull; \u003Ca href=\"http:\u002F\u002Fwww.bbc.com\u002Ffuture\u002Fstory\u002F20180725-the-health-condition-vulvodynia-is-painful-and-misunderstood\" target=\"_blank\"\u003EThe excruciating condition that only affects women\u003C\u002Fa\u003E\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003EMarker scoured the land for alternatives, examining more than 400 species, but to no avail. Then he stumbled upon a drawing in an obscure botany book. This yam had fat, knobbly roots that reportedly weighed up to 100 kg (220lbs). He travelled to its native Mexico and smuggled one out of the country.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWith an affordable source of progesterone found, researchers turned to its uses as a contraceptive. The birth control pill hit the market less than a decade later. Marker, on the other hand, mysteriously disappeared from public life and became obsessed with \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.acs.org\u002Fcontent\u002Facs\u002Fen\u002Feducation\u002Fwhatischemistry\u002Flandmarks\u002Fprogesteronesynthesis.html\" target=\"_blank\"\u003Ecollecting silver\u003C\u002Fa\u003E. &nbsp;&nbsp;\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe economic and social side effects of the pill were as profound as they are well-documented. Sex could be enjoyed without fear of pregnancy. Suddenly women could devote their 20s and 30s to furthering their education and careers, rather than housework and nappies.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E"},"cardType":"Body","iFrameType":"","id":"future\u002Farticle\u002F20180822-the-birth-control-pill-can-have-male-side-effects-0"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[]},"cardType":"Image","iFrameType":"","image":[],"imageAlignment":"centre","id":"future\u002Farticle\u002F20180822-the-birth-control-pill-can-have-male-side-effects-1"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[],"html":"\u003Cp\u003EBut right from the beginning, the pill has had a secret.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIn recent years, scientists have started to realise that the brains of women on the pill look fundamentally different. Compared to women who aren&rsquo;t taking hormones, some regions of their brains seem to be \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov\u002Fpmc\u002Farticles\u002FPMC4113343\u002F\" target=\"_blank\"\u003Emore typically &lsquo;male&rsquo;\u003C\u002Fa\u003E.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThere are behavioural changes, too. Women on certain types of pill aren&rsquo;t as good at coming up with words &ndash; something our gender are usually highly skilled at. On the other hand, they&rsquo;re better at mentally rotating objects, as is often the case in men. Finally, women on a different type of pill are better at recognising faces &ndash; something women are usually good at. &nbsp;\u003C\u002Fp\u003E"},"cardType":"Body","iFrameType":"","id":"future\u002Farticle\u002F20180822-the-birth-control-pill-can-have-male-side-effects-2"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[]},"cardType":"Image","iFrameType":"","image":[],"imageAlignment":"centre","id":"future\u002Farticle\u002F20180822-the-birth-control-pill-can-have-male-side-effects-3"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[],"html":"\u003Cp\u003EConfused? So are scientists. What&rsquo;s going on?\u003C\u002Fp\u003E"},"cardType":"Body","iFrameType":"","id":"future\u002Farticle\u002F20180822-the-birth-control-pill-can-have-male-side-effects-4"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[]},"cardType":"PullQuote","iFrameType":"","pullQuote":"We&rsquo;re often told that the pill contains oestrogen and progesterone. But no pill contains either hormone","id":"future\u002Farticle\u002F20180822-the-birth-control-pill-can-have-male-side-effects-5"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[],"html":"\u003Cp\u003EWe&rsquo;re often told that the pill contains oestrogen and progesterone. But no pill contains either hormone.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThat is because, when taken orally, oestrogen and progesterone break down too quickly to be practical. Instead, the pill contains synthetic versions, which are \u003Ca href=\"http:\u002F\u002Fwww.kup.at\u002Fkup\u002Fpdf\u002F10165.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"\u003Ebuilt from more stable hormones\u003C\u002Fa\u003E that have been altered to mimic the hormones.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003EEvery brand of combined pill on the market contains the same type of synthetic oestrogen, ethinyl estradiol, and one of eight synthetic progesterones, called progestins. Ethinyl estradiol prevents the body from releasing an egg every month, while progestins thicken the mucus at the entrance to the cervix and conspire to make the womb inhospitable. Even if an egg slips out and becomes fertilised, it won&rsquo;t be able to settle down and start growing.&nbsp;&nbsp;\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003ESo far, so good. But though the hormones are effective at preventing pregnancy, they aren&rsquo;t perfect matches for our natural hormones. The end result is that these synthetic versions also have effects that you would never get from raw progesterone.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E"},"cardType":"Body","iFrameType":"","id":"future\u002Farticle\u002F20180822-the-birth-control-pill-can-have-male-side-effects-6"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[]},"cardType":"Image","iFrameType":"","image":[],"imageAlignment":"centre","id":"future\u002Farticle\u002F20180822-the-birth-control-pill-can-have-male-side-effects-7"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[],"html":"\u003Cp\u003EThe internet is awash with anecdotal reports of acne, sweating and unwanted hair growth after going on the pill. One women described \u003Ca href=\"http:\u002F\u002Fwww.hairtell.com\u002Fforum\u002Fubbthreads.php\u002Ftopics\u002F92873\u002FOrtho_Tri_Cyclen_gave_me_facia.html\" target=\"_blank\"\u003Esprouting hairs all over her cheeks\u003C\u002Fa\u003E, while another \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.reddit.com\u002Fr\u002FSkincareAddiction\u002Fcomments\u002F2qsdta\u002Fladies_how_have_birth_control_pills_affected_your\u002F\" target=\"_blank\"\u003Ecame down with &ldquo;pizza face&rdquo;\u003C\u002Fa\u003E after starting a new brand. These &lsquo;masculine&rsquo; effects have been well-studied by scientists, and they are real: certain kinds of pill really do make them worse, especially in susceptible women.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cem\u003EFind out more: eight women open up about the side effects they struggled with from the pill in our recent video, below.\u003C\u002Fem\u003E\u003C\u002Fp\u003E"},"cardType":"Body","iFrameType":"","id":"future\u002Farticle\u002F20180822-the-birth-control-pill-can-have-male-side-effects-8"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[]},"cardType":"Video","iFrameType":"","videoImageAlign":"centre","videoUrn":[],"id":"future\u002Farticle\u002F20180822-the-birth-control-pill-can-have-male-side-effects-9"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[],"html":"\u003Cp\u003EBut the reason is surprising. According to a \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov\u002Fpmc\u002Farticles\u002FPMC3469779\u002F\" target=\"_blank\"\u003Estudy from 2012\u003C\u002Fa\u003E, 83% of US women who are on the pill are taking a version that contains progestins made from male hormones. This includes the popular brands Ortho Tri-Cyclen, Loestrin FE 1\u002F20 and Tri-Sprintec&reg;, among many others.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe male hormone that these pills use is a close relative of testosterone called nandrolone. A potent androgen (a hormone that influences the development of the male reproductive system), it can lead to the development of typically male characteristics.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E"},"cardType":"Body","iFrameType":"","id":"future\u002Farticle\u002F20180822-the-birth-control-pill-can-have-male-side-effects-10"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[]},"cardType":"PullQuote","iFrameType":"","pullQuote":"It&rsquo;s actually used for doping in men sometimes &mdash; Belinda Pletzer","id":"future\u002Farticle\u002F20180822-the-birth-control-pill-can-have-male-side-effects-11"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[],"html":"\u003Cp\u003E&ldquo;It&rsquo;s actually used for doping in men sometimes,&rdquo; says Belinda Pletzer, a cognitive neuroscientist at the University of Salzburg, Austria. It helps build muscle, so it&rsquo;s popular with powerlifters and boxers: the former heavyweight world champion Tyson Fury recently served a two-year suspension after testing \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.theguardian.com\u002Fsport\u002F2017\u002Fdec\u002F12\u002Ftyson-fury-doping-hearing-failure-to-appear-boxing\" target=\"_blank\"\u003Epositive for the steroid in 2015\u003C\u002Fa\u003E (he claimed it entered his system after eating the meat of an uncastrated wild boar.)\u003C\u002Fp\u003E"},"cardType":"Body","iFrameType":"","id":"future\u002Farticle\u002F20180822-the-birth-control-pill-can-have-male-side-effects-12"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[]},"cardType":"Image","iFrameType":"","image":[],"imageAlignment":"centre","id":"future\u002Farticle\u002F20180822-the-birth-control-pill-can-have-male-side-effects-13"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[],"html":"\u003Cp\u003EWe&rsquo;ve known about these side effects for decades: the first progestin ever made, norethindrone, was androgenic.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003EBack in the 1940s, 50s and 60s, pregnant women sometimes took norethindrone in large doses to help prevent miscarriage. But the hormone also caused some unsettling changes to their bodies.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe women were sweatier, hairier and spottier. Some noticed that their voices had deepened. Nearly \u003Ca href=\"http:\u002F\u002Fwww.ajog.org\u002Farticle\u002F0002-9378(62)90075-3\u002Fpdf\" target=\"_blank\"\u003Eone in five baby girls\u003C\u002Fa\u003E born to mothers taking it had masculinised genitals. Some of these unlucky children \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.tandfonline.com\u002Fdoi\u002Fabs\u002F10.1080\u002F00224496709550517?journalCode=hjsr20\" target=\"_blank\"\u003Erequired surgery\u003C\u002Fa\u003E.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003EToday androgenic progestins are much less androgenic. The doses in contraceptive pills are much smaller, and the hormones are usually combined with synthetic oestrogen, which cancels out many of the masculine effects on our bodies.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003EBut there are some side effects.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003E&ldquo;These progestins, which were decreased in dose over the years, are still related to the chemical structure of testosterone. All the derivatives came out to levonorgestrel, which is the most used or known of the progestins,&rdquo; says Regine&nbsp;Sitruk-Ware, a reproductive endocrinologist at the Population Council, New York. &ldquo;It is still androgenic by itself, by the fact that it can bind to the androgen receptors.&rdquo;\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOver the years, there have been several generations of progestins. Though the earlier ones are nearly all androgenic, more recently scientists have developed versions made from synthetic progesterone, instead. These have the opposite effects &ndash; they are often prescribed to treat acne or excessive hair growth because they are &lsquo;feminising&rsquo; (though they, too, \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.acne.org\u002Fmessageboard\u002Ftopic\u002F213589-yasmin-and-hair-loss\u002F\"\u003Ecan have undesireable side effects resulting from a hormonal imbalance\u003C\u002Fa\u003E). Some examples include Yasmin&reg; and Ocella&trade;.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E"},"cardType":"Body","iFrameType":"","id":"future\u002Farticle\u002F20180822-the-birth-control-pill-can-have-male-side-effects-14"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[]},"cardType":"Image","iFrameType":"","image":[],"imageAlignment":"centre","id":"future\u002Farticle\u002F20180822-the-birth-control-pill-can-have-male-side-effects-15"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[],"html":"\u003Cp\u003EGenerally speaking, the older, cheaper brands of pill tend to contain androgenic hormones, while newer, more expensive ones tend to contain anti-androgens. This may be one reason that \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov\u002Fpmc\u002Farticles\u002FPMC3469779\u002F\" target=\"_blank\"\u003Ejust 17% of women on the combined pill\u003C\u002Fa\u003E in the US take the anti-androgenic versions.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThere are androgen receptors all over the body, particularly in the sweat glands and hair follicles, which explains why androgenic progestins can make some women sweatier, hairier and spottier. But these powerful, gender-bending steroids also affect the brain.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIn men, the androgens released at puberty are known to \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.sciencedirect.com\u002Fscience\u002Farticle\u002Fpii\u002FS0091302205000488\" target=\"_blank\"\u003Eremodel the brain\u003C\u002Fa\u003E. This is also true in women, where relatively small quantities of testosterone can cause certain areas to \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.sciencedaily.com\u002Freleases\u002F2015\u002F08\u002F150831001124.htm\" target=\"_blank\"\u003Eshrink and others to grow\u003C\u002Fa\u003E.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E"},"cardType":"Body","iFrameType":"","id":"future\u002Farticle\u002F20180822-the-birth-control-pill-can-have-male-side-effects-16"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[]},"cardType":"Image","iFrameType":"","image":[],"imageAlignment":"centre","id":"future\u002Farticle\u002F20180822-the-birth-control-pill-can-have-male-side-effects-17"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[],"html":"\u003Cp\u003EGiven what we know about the power of these hormones, it&rsquo;s perhaps surprising that until recently, no one had checked if progestins made from male hormones might have an impact.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003E&ldquo;There has been a lot of research on their physical side effects,&rdquo; says Pletzer. &ldquo;There&rsquo;s also been research on the emotional side effects, because that&rsquo;s something that women keep complaining about. But very few studies have looked at the brain and cognition.&rdquo;\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOne of the first such studies was \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.sciencedirect.com\u002Fscience\u002Farticle\u002Fpii\u002FS0006899310013545\" target=\"_blank\"\u003Econducted only eight years ago\u003C\u002Fa\u003E &ndash; after the pill had already been in use for 50 years. At the time Pletzer was interested in how women&rsquo;s brains change throughout the menstrual cycle. \u003Cem\u003E(Read more about \u003C\u002Fem\u003E\u003Cem\u003E\u003Ca href=\"http:\u002F\u002Fwww.bbc.com\u002Ffuture\u002Fstory\u002F20180806-how-the-menstrual-cycle-changes-womens-brains-every-month\" target=\"_blank\"\u003Ehow the menstrual cycle changes women&rsquo;s brains and abilities\u003C\u002Fa\u003E\u003C\u002Fem\u003E\u003Cem\u003E over the course of the month).\u003C\u002Fem\u003E\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003EBut when she realised she was excluding those on the pill, she asked herself why. &ldquo;We know that the steroids our own body produces, such as progesterone and testosterone, affect the brain. So of course I would expect any synthetic hormones to have an effect as well,&rdquo; she says. &nbsp;\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003EPletzer abandoned her original idea and set out to test the effects of the pill instead. She recruited a mixture of men and women on and off hormonal contraception, then scanned their brains.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhat she found was striking. The scans revealed that several brain areas were larger in the women on the pill, compared to those of women who weren&rsquo;t. These areas just so happened to be larger in men than women, too.&nbsp;\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe study involved a relatively small sample and didn&rsquo;t separate androgenic and anti-androgenic contraception, so Pletzer cautions against reading too much into the results. But other research has hinted that both types of hormones actually may be changing our behaviour.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E"},"cardType":"Body","iFrameType":"","id":"future\u002Farticle\u002F20180822-the-birth-control-pill-can-have-male-side-effects-18"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[]},"cardType":"Image","iFrameType":"","image":[],"imageAlignment":"centre","id":"future\u002Farticle\u002F20180822-the-birth-control-pill-can-have-male-side-effects-19"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[],"html":"&shy;&shy;\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIt turns out that women taking pills with androgenic progestins have \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.psyneuen-journal.com\u002Farticle\u002FS0306-4530(11)00089-8\u002Fabstract\" target=\"_blank\"\u003Elower verbal fluency\u003C\u002Fa\u003E (the ability to think of new words). They were also better at rotating objects. This makes sense, since men are thought to be \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Flink.springer.com\u002Farticle\u002F10.1007%2Fs10339-017-0801-1\" target=\"_blank\"\u003Eslightly less articulate than women\u003C\u002Fa\u003E in certain situations and have \u003Ca href=\"http:\u002F\u002Fict.usc.edu\u002Fpubs\u002FSex%20differences%20in%20mental%20rotation%20and%20spatial%20rotation%20in%20a%20virtual%20environment.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"\u003Ebetter spatial awareness\u003C\u002Fa\u003E.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E"},"cardType":"Body","iFrameType":"","id":"future\u002Farticle\u002F20180822-the-birth-control-pill-can-have-male-side-effects-20"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[]},"cardType":"PullQuote","iFrameType":"","pullQuote":"Other studies have found that women on oral contraception remember emotional stories more like men","id":"future\u002Farticle\u002F20180822-the-birth-control-pill-can-have-male-side-effects-21"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[],"html":"\u003Cp\u003EOther studies have found that \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov\u002Fpubmed\u002F21740976\" target=\"_blank\"\u003Ewomen on oral contraception\u003C\u002Fa\u003E remember emotional stories \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.sciencedirect.com\u002Fscience\u002Farticle\u002Fpii\u002FS1074742711001249\" target=\"_blank\"\u003Emore like men\u003C\u002Fa\u003E &ndash; recalling the gist more than the details. They&rsquo;re also not as good at recognising emotions in others, such as \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.sciencedirect.com\u002Fscience\u002Farticle\u002Fpii\u002FS0924977X14002491\" target=\"_blank\"\u003Eanger, sadness, or disgust\u003C\u002Fa\u003E &ndash; \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov\u002Fpmc\u002Farticles\u002FPMC5749848\u002F\" target=\"_blank\"\u003Ejust like men\u003C\u002Fa\u003E. It looks suspiciously like certain types of pill are &ldquo;masculinising&rdquo; women&rsquo;s brains.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E"},"cardType":"Body","iFrameType":"","id":"future\u002Farticle\u002F20180822-the-birth-control-pill-can-have-male-side-effects-22"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[]},"cardType":"Image","iFrameType":"","image":[],"imageAlignment":"centre","id":"future\u002Farticle\u002F20180822-the-birth-control-pill-can-have-male-side-effects-23"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[],"html":"\u003Cp\u003EPerhaps the most striking evidence, however, comes from a paper published in 2015. This time, \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.sciencedirect.com\u002Fscience\u002Farticle\u002Fpii\u002FS0006899314016096\" target=\"_blank\"\u003EPletzer compared the brains of women on the two types of pill with women who were not\u003C\u002Fa\u003E. Several brain areas were larger in the women whose pills contained the newer, anti-androgenic progestins.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003ECrucially, these changes seemed to be affecting their behaviour.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003ETwo brain areas were particularly engorged: the fusiform face area, a region about the size of a pea that processes facial information (from photographs of friends to cartoons), and the parahippocampal place area, which important for recognising places (such as cityscapes). These women were also better at recognising faces.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003EFacial recognition is something women are \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.tandfonline.com\u002Fdoi\u002Fabs\u002F10.1080\u002F13506285.2013.823140?journalCode=pvis20\" target=\"_blank\"\u003Eusually highly skilled at\u003C\u002Fa\u003E &ndash; \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov\u002Fpubmed\u002F10825784\" target=\"_blank\"\u003Eeven as babies\u003C\u002Fa\u003E &ndash; so this fits with the picture of oral contraceptives subtly influencing our brains. In this case, the anti-androgenic pills may be having a &ldquo;feminising&rdquo; effect.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E"},"cardType":"Body","iFrameType":"","id":"future\u002Farticle\u002F20180822-the-birth-control-pill-can-have-male-side-effects-24"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[]},"cardType":"Image","iFrameType":"","image":[],"imageAlignment":"centre","id":"future\u002Farticle\u002F20180822-the-birth-control-pill-can-have-male-side-effects-25"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[],"html":"\u003Cp\u003EJust as before, several brain areas were also larger in women on androgenic pills, including many which are typically so in men. The longer the women had been on the pill, the larger these areas were.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003ETo complicate matters further, all combined pills contain synthetic oestrogen, which is feminising. This means that the same women may be experiencing both &lsquo;feminising&rsquo; and &lsquo;masculinising&rsquo; effects on their brains at the same time.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003ENo one could have predicted that an ugly yam would give rise to a feminist revolution. The pill has repeatedly been called the \u003Ca href=\"http:\u002F\u002Fwww.bbc.co.uk\u002Fnews\u002Fuk-15984258\" target=\"_blank\"\u003Egreatest invention of the 20th Century\u003C\u002Fa\u003E and is said to be \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.forbes.com\u002Fforbes\u002Fwelcome\u002F?toURL=https:\u002F\u002Fwww.forbes.com\u002Fsites\u002Fmeghancasserly\u002F2012\u002F03\u002F30\u002Fcontraception-womens-earnings-martha-bailey-healthcare\u002F&amp;refURL=https:\u002F\u002Fwww.google.co.uk\u002F&amp;referrer=https:\u002F\u002Fwww.google.co.uk\u002F\" target=\"_blank\"\u003Eresponsible for a third\u003C\u002Fa\u003E of the increase in women&rsquo;s wages since the 1960s.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003EBut contraceptive pills may have a darker side. As Pletzer \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.frontiersin.org\u002Farticles\u002F10.3389\u002Ffnins.2014.00256\u002Ffull\" target=\"_blank\"\u003Ewrote in 2014\u003C\u002Fa\u003E, when athletes take steroids we call it &lsquo;doping&rsquo; &ndash; it&rsquo;s considered abuse and strongly condemned by society. But we&rsquo;re happy for millions of women to take these hormones every day, sometimes right through from puberty to menopause.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003EScientists don&rsquo;t yet know if any of the pill&rsquo;s effects on the brain have much of an impact on our behaviour. But perhaps it is time we put it to the test.&nbsp;\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cem\u003ECorrection: An earlier version of this story implied that the 'feminising' effects of pills like Yasmin could lead to hair loss; while some women do experience hair loss while taking birth control pills, this tends to be for broader reasons \u003Ca href=\"http:\u002F\u002Fwww.americanhairloss.org\u002Fwomen_hair_loss\u002Foral_contraceptives.asp\"\u003Esuch as a resulting hormonal balance. \u003C\u002Fa\u003EThis has been changed.\u003Cbr \u002F\u003E\u003C\u002Fem\u003E\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cem\u003EThis story is part of the \u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Ca href=\"http:\u002F\u002Fbbc.com\u002Ffuture\u002Fstory\u002F20180521-the-health-gap-how-women-experience-the-medical-system\" target=\"_blank\"\u003EHealth Gap\u003C\u002Fa\u003E,\u003C\u002Fstrong\u003E a special series about how men and women experience the medical system &ndash; and their own health &ndash; in starkly different ways.\u003C\u002Fem\u003E\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cem\u003EDo you have an experience to share? Or are you just interested in sharing information about women's health and wellbeing? Join our Facebook group\u003Cstrong\u003E \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fbbc.in\u002F2LQHVAC\" target=\"_blank\"\u003EFuture Woman\u003C\u002Fa\u003E \u003C\u002Fstrong\u003Eand be a part of the conversation about the day-to-day issues that affect women&rsquo;s lives.&nbsp;\u003C\u002Fem\u003E\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cem\u003EJoin 