ose when the organ wandered around the body, becoming trapped in different body parts. The latter belief persisted well into the 19th Century, when the disorder was famously treated by bringing women to \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.theguardian.com\u002Flifeandstyle\u002F2012\u002Fsep\u002F07\u002Fhow-the-vibrator-caused-buzz\"\u003Eorgasm with early vibrators\u003C\u002Fa\u003E.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003EEven today, the notion that a woman&rsquo;s biology can befuddle her brain is a staple of popular culture. If a woman is moody, she&rsquo;s asked if it&rsquo;s &lsquo;that time of the month&rsquo;. If she&rsquo;s feeling sexual, she&rsquo;s told she might be ovulating.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cem\u003EYou might also like these other stories in the \u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Ca href=\"http:\u002F\u002Fwww.bbc.com\u002Ffuture\u002Fstory\u002F20180521-the-health-gap-how-women-experience-the-medical-system\" target=\"_blank\"\u003EHealth Gap\u003C\u002Fa\u003E:\u003C\u002Fstrong\u003E\u003C\u002Fem\u003E\u003Cbr \u002F\u003E&bull; \u003Ca href=\"http:\u002F\u002Fwww.bbc.com\u002Ffuture\u002Fstory\u002F20180705-why-dementia-and-alzheimers-affect-women-more-than-men\"\u003EWhy does Alzheimer&rsquo;s hit women harder?\u003C\u002Fa\u003E\u003Cbr \u002F\u003E&bull; \u003Ca href=\"http:\u002F\u002Fwww.bbc.com\u002Ffuture\u002Fstory\u002F20180702-the-sexist-history-of-migraine-may-affect-research-today\"\u003EThe enduring mystery of migraines\u003C\u002Fa\u003E\u003Cbr \u002F\u003E&bull; \u003Ca href=\"http:\u002F\u002Fwww.bbc.com\u002Ffuture\u002Fstory\u002F20180611-the-health-risks-of-girls-maturing-early\"\u003EThe health risks of maturing early\u003C\u002Fa\u003E\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIt turns out this isn&rsquo;t unfounded &ndash; some women really do \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.tandfonline.com\u002Fdoi\u002Fabs\u002F10.1080\u002F03630242.2015.1101739\"\u003Efeel more anxious and irritable\u003C\u002Fa\u003E around their period, and 