,"longitude":"","mpsVideo":"","option":[],"partner":null,"primaryVertical":"future","promoAlignment":"centre","promoAltText":"","promoImage":null,"relatedStories":null,"relatedTag":null,"summaryLong":"Right after a period, women have better spatial awareness. Three weeks after, verbal skills peak. It turns out the monthly cycle does change the brain – but not in the ways you think.","summaryShort":"Memory, communication and creativity are just some skills that are transformed","tag":[],"creationDateTime":"2018-08-07T01:18:59.376807Z","entity":"article","guid":"6906c3b6-ff6e-48f4-ae39-75a40187af9a","id":"future\u002Farticle\u002F20180806-how-the-menstrual-cycle-changes-womens-brains-every-month","modifiedDateTime":"2019-10-04T14:28:01.446304Z","project":"future","slug":"20180806-how-the-menstrual-cycle-changes-womens-brains-every-month","cacheLastUpdated":1587443048838},"future\u002Farticle\u002F20181003-does-the-birth-control-pill-make-you-fat":{"urn":"urn:pubstack:jative:article:future\u002Farticle\u002F20181003-does-the-birth-control-pill-make-you-fat","_id":"5e98209b8ec3f2455a11c0e4","ambientVideo":"","articleType":"story","assetVideo":null,"author":["future\u002Fauthor\u002Fzaria-gorvett"],"bodyIntro":"Many women believe that the pill can cause weight gain. Research hasn’t found this – but it has found that it can change body shape (and fat storage) in other surprising ways.","businessUnit":"worldwide","cards":[{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[],"html":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\"http:\u002F\u002Fwww.bbc.com\u002Ffuture\u002Fstory\u002F20180521-the-health-gap-how-women-experience-the-medical-system\"\u003E\u003Cimg src=\"http:\u002F\u002Fichef.bbci.co.uk\u002Fimages\u002Fic\u002Fraw\u002Fp067ssc1.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"&ldquo;The\" width=\"100%\" \u002F\u003E\u003C\u002Fa\u003E\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIt&rsquo;s been blamed for \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.livescience.com\u002F20532-birth-control-water-pollution.html\"\u003Epolluting our rivers\u003C\u002Fa\u003E, \u003Ca href=\"http:\u002F\u002Fwww.dailymail.co.uk\u002Ffemail\u002Farticle-1276838\u002FThe-Pill-ruined-institution-marriage-says-Raquel-Welch.html\"\u003Edestroying our marriages\u003C\u002Fa\u003E and &ndash; ironically &ndash; killing our sex drives. It&rsquo;s been called a \u003Ca href=\"http:\u002F\u002Fwww.slate.com\u002Farticles\u002Fdouble_x\u002Fdoublex\u002F2013\u002F09\u002F_sweetening_the_pill_by_holly_grigg_spall_reviewed.html\"\u003Econspiracy by the patriarchy\u003C\u002Fa\u003E. It&rsquo;s even be accused of \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.elle.com\u002Flife-love\u002Fsex-relationships\u002Fnews\u002Fa19960\u002Fbirth-control-pill-changes-what-women-consider-attractive\u002F\"\u003Emaking women fancy ugly men\u003C\u002Fa\u003E. But for many women, one of the most off-putting charges against the contraceptive pill is that it makes us fat.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIn fact, weight gain is the most commonly reported side effect of the combined pill &ndash; the most popular type, which contains both lab-made oestrogen and progesterone. This is why pharmaceutical companies list it on the packet.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003EBut after several decades of research, there still \u003Ca href=\"http:\u002F\u002Fwww.cochrane.org\u002FCD003987\u002FFERTILREG_effect-of-birth-control-pills-and-patches-on-weight\"\u003Eisn&rsquo;t any conclusive evidence\u003C\u002Fa\u003E that the effect is real. The largest review so far examined 49 studies of the combined pill and found &ldquo;no large effect is evident&rdquo;, but also that there wasn&rsquo;t enough well-conducted research to be sure. The researchers found this is true no matter what type of progesterone the combined pill contained (for more on the different kinds of pill, check out \u003Ca href=\"http:\u002F\u002Fwww.bbc.com\u002Ffuture\u002Fstory\u002F20180822-the-birth-control-pill-can-have-male-side-effects\"\u003Ethis article\u003C\u002Fa\u003E). Other studies that looked at progesterone-only pills similarly have found little evidence of an effect.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cem\u003EYou might also like these other stories in the \u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Ca href=\"http:\u002F\u002Fwww.bbc.com\u002Ffuture\u002Fstory\u002F20180521-the-health-gap-how-women-experience-the-medical-system\" target=\"_blank\"\u003EHealth Gap\u003C\u002Fa\u003E:\u003Cbr \u002F\u003E\u003C\u002Fstrong\u003E\u003C\u002Fem\u003E&bull; \u003Ca href=\" http:\u002F\u002Fwww.bbc.com\u002Ffuture\u002Fstory\u002F20180822-the-birth-control-pill-can-have-male-side-effects \" target=\"_blank\"\u003EThe strange truth about the pill\u003C\u002Fa\u003E\u003Cbr \u002F\u003E&bull; \u003Ca href=\" http:\u002F\u002Fwww.bbc.com\u002Ffuture\u002Fstory\u002F20180806-how-the-menstrual-cycle-changes-womens-brains-every-month\" target=\"_blank\"\u003EHow the menstrual cycle changes women&rsquo;s brains\u003C\u002Fa\u003E\u003Cbr \u002F\u003E&bull; \u003Ca href=\"http:\u002F\u002Fwww.bbc.com\u002Ffuture\u002Fstory\u002F20180830-what-to-know-about-the-coil-or-iud-contraceptive-method\"\u003EWhy isn't this type of birth control used more?\u003C\u002Fa\u003E\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003EMaria Gallo, an endocrinologist at Ohio State University who co-authored the review, believes our belief in the pill-weight connection is down to a natural human bias. People are experts at finding patterns all around us, even where there are none. The phenomenon, known as apophenia, is the reason we may find it easy to \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.buzzfeed.com\u002Fgreggdd69\u002F7-peppers-that-look-like-british-politicians-5v0w?utm_term=.ah2P8XKKR#.mt6PZ744Y\"\u003Ecompare peppers to politicians\u003C\u002Fa\u003E, see the faces of \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.dailystar.co.uk\u002Fnews\u002Flatest-news\u002F506793\u002FHarry-Potter-arch-nemesis-Voldemort-weird-cloud-shape\"\u003EHarry Potter villains\u003C\u002Fa\u003E staring down at us from the clouds, or read too much into past lottery numbers. We&rsquo;re particularly susceptible to apophenia if we&rsquo;ve been primed to expect a certain outcome &ndash; such as gaining weight after starting a new medication.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003E&ldquo;It&rsquo;s the same reason why there&rsquo;s this idea that vaccines can cause health problems,&rdquo; says Maria Gallo. &ldquo;If you give them to a population, you&rsquo;re going to have some people who have health problems, whether they&rsquo;re linked to the vaccine or not.&rdquo;\u003C\u002Fp\u003E"},"cardType":"Body","iFrameType":"","id":"future\u002Farticle\u002F20181003-does-the-birth-control-pill-make-you-fat-0"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[]},"cardType":"Image","iFrameType":"","image":["p06mvkr4"],"imageAlignment":"centre","id":"future\u002Farticle\u002F20181003-does-the-birth-control-pill-make-you-fat-1"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[],"html":"\u003Cp\u003EIn the case of the pill, Gallo points out that \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.nejm.org\u002Fdoi\u002Ffull\u002F10.1056\u002FNejmoa1014296\"\u003Ethe average person puts on just over a pound\u003C\u002Fa\u003E (half a kilo) of weight each year for most of their life, starting in early adulthood &ndash; which, incidentally, is when most women start using contraception. It may be reassuring to be able to blame this &lsquo;weight creep&rsquo; on something other than overeating; last year she even caught women in the act of \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov\u002Fpubmed\u002F26855107\"\u003Einventing weight gain after being fitted with the contraceptive implant\u003C\u002Fa\u003E.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003EEven so, it&rsquo;s not all in our heads. Though large-scale reviews haven&rsquo;t found that the pill causes weight gain, it \u003Cem\u003Ecan\u003C\u002Fem\u003E change a woman&rsquo;s body shape and composition.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThere are three big reasons for this, and they have to do with muscle, fluid retention, and fat.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMuscle in\u003C\u002Fstrong\u003E\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003EBack in 2009, Steven Riechman, an exercise physiologist at Texas A&amp;M University, discovered one surprising impact of the pill, entirely by accident.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E"},"cardType":"Body","iFrameType":"","id":"future\u002Farticle\u002F20181003-does-the-birth-control-pill-make-you-fat-2"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[]},"cardType":"PullQuote","iFrameType":"","pullQuote":"Women on the pill had gained 40% less muscle than those who weren&rsquo;t on it","id":"future\u002Farticle\u002F20181003-does-the-birth-control-pill-make-you-fat-3"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[],"html":"\u003Cp\u003EAt the time, he was researching how a person&rsquo;s genetic makeup can \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.fasebj.org\u002Fdoi\u002Fabs\u002F10.1096\u002Ffasebj.23.1_supplement.955.25\"\u003Eaffect their ability to grow their muscles through exercise\u003C\u002Fa\u003E. His research team put a group of men and women through 10 weeks of resistance training &ndash; slow, punishing exercises such as \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.livestrong.com\u002Farticle\u002F338918-the-proper-form-for-an-abdominal-crunch\u002F\"\u003Ecrunches\u003C\u002Fa\u003E and lifting heavy weights. Then participants were weighed to see if they had more muscle than they started with. The team also gathered information on various lifestyle factors so that they could make sure any gains were caused by genetics and not, for example, the medications they were on.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhile they were doing this analysis, they discovered that women on the pill had gained 40% less muscle than those who weren&rsquo;t on it.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003E&ldquo;It jumped out as a pretty big impact,&rdquo; says Riechman.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cem\u003EEight women open up about the side effects they experienced from the pill. Watch the video below.\u003C\u002Fem\u003E\u003C\u002Fp\u003E"},"cardType":"Body","iFrameType":"","id":"future\u002Farticle\u002F20181003-does-the-birth-control-pill-make-you-fat-4"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[]},"cardType":"Video","iFrameType":"","videoImageAlign":"centre","videoUrn":["p06jbqf7"],"id":"future\u002Farticle\u002F20181003-does-the-birth-control-pill-make-you-fat-5"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[],"html":"\u003Cp\u003EIt&rsquo;s well-known that men naturally have more muscle than women. \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov\u002Fpubmed\u002F10904038\"\u003EThe average man has 72lbs (33kg) of brawn\u003C\u002Fa\u003E, compared with a measly 46lbs (21kg) in women. This is partly just because men are taller and heavier overall, but that isn&rsquo;t the whole story &ndash; as a percentage of overall body mass, \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.physiology.org\u002Fdoi\u002F10.1152\u002Fjappl.2000.89.1.81\"\u003Emen are about 38% muscle\u003C\u002Fa\u003E while women are 31%. This comes down to hormones: men have more &lsquo;anabolic&rsquo; hormones running through their veins, which tell the body when to grow more muscle.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E"},"cardType":"Body","iFrameType":"","id":"future\u002Farticle\u002F20181003-does-the-birth-control-pill-make-you-fat-6"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[]},"cardType":"Image","iFrameType":"","image":["p06mvksp"],"imageAlignment":"centre","id":"future\u002Farticle\u002F20181003-does-the-birth-control-pill-make-you-fat-7"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[],"html":"\u003Cp\u003EThis includes an important but little-known steroid called DHEA. It&rsquo;s secreted by the adrenal glands &ndash; cocktail sausage-sized organs which sit above each kidney &ndash; and is involved in everything from keeping bones strong to maintaining our immune systems.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe hormone used to be extremely popular with athletes, partly because of its extraordinary muscle-building power, and partly because \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.nytimes.com\u002F2005\u002F04\u002F17\u002Fus\u002Fhow-one-pill-escaped-the-list-of-controlled-steroids.html\"\u003Edoping with it was legal\u003C\u002Fa\u003E until fairly recently. Just in case you were getting any ideas, it also has many drawbacks, such as the tendency to cause liver damage and \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.livestrong.com\u002Farticle\u002F364390-dhea-supplements-male-fertility\u002F\"\u003Eshrink a man&rsquo;s testicles\u003C\u002Fa\u003E.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003EBut women produce anabolic hormones too &ndash; and the team found that those on the pill had much lower levels of DHEA in their blood.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E"},"cardType":"Body","iFrameType":"","id":"future\u002Farticle\u002F20181003-does-the-birth-control-pill-make-you-fat-8"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[]},"cardType":"Image","iFrameType":"","image":["p06mvl3c"],"imageAlignment":"centre","id":"future\u002Farticle\u002F20181003-does-the-birth-control-pill-make-you-fat-9"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[],"html":"\u003Cp\u003EEven more intriguingly, the poor muscle gains weren&rsquo;t found in all women on the pill, just those that contained a certain type of lab-made progesterone that likes to bind to the same protein.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003E&ldquo;We&rsquo;re pretty confident the progesterone is what&rsquo;s causing this,&rdquo; says Riechman. One possibility is that by competing for the same binding sites, the hormone may be blocking signals to grow more muscle. The results haven&rsquo;t definitively proven the link, but if it does turn out to be real, surely women will want to know about it &ndash; especially in the light of recent fitness obsessions such as \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fedition.cnn.com\u002F2017\u002F05\u002F01\u002Fsport\u002Fhow-to-talk-to-someone-who-does-crossfit\u002Findex.html\"\u003ECrossFit\u003C\u002Fa\u003E and Instagramming your abs. &ldquo;This study should absolutely be followed up. People are interested and we get calls fairly regularly about it,&rdquo; he says.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFat storage\u003C\u002Fstrong\u003E\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAnd the pill may be changing women&rsquo;s bodies in other ways, too. Just as it has an impact on the proportion of muscle in our bodies, it could be exerting subtle influences on fat &ndash; particularly where it is stored in the body.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E"},"cardType":"Body","iFrameType":"","id":"future\u002Farticle\u002F20181003-does-the-birth-control-pill-make-you-fat-10"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[]},"cardType":"PullQuote","iFrameType":"","pullQuote":"The pill could be exerting subtle influences on fat &ndash; particularly where it is stored in the body","id":"future\u002Farticle\u002F20181003-does-the-birth-control-pill-make-you-fat-11"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[],"html":"\u003Cp\u003EAt puberty, oestrogen and progesterone are responsible for the development of typically &lsquo;female&rsquo; characteristics, such as wider hips and larger breasts, largely by changing the way fat is distributed. The hormones are also often given to transsexuals for the same reason.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe womanly &lsquo;hourglass figure&rsquo; emerges as \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov\u002Fpmc\u002Farticles\u002FPMC4507503\u002F\"\u003Edifferent kinds of fat tissue respond differently to these reproductive hormones\u003C\u002Fa\u003E. For example, subcutaneous fat &ndash; the kind of chub that women carry around their thighs, hips and breasts &ndash; contains lots of oestrogen receptors.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E"},"cardType":"Body","iFrameType":"","id":"future\u002Farticle\u002F20181003-does-the-birth-control-pill-make-you-fat-12"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[]},"cardType":"Image","iFrameType":"","image":["p06mvl5r"],"imageAlignment":"centre","id":"future\u002Farticle\u002F20181003-does-the-birth-control-pill-make-you-fat-13"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[],"html":"\u003Cp\u003EIt&rsquo;s easy to see how, theoretically, changing a woman&rsquo;s hormone balance could alter where her fat is stored. Some research has borne this out: one early study found that women on pills with higher levels of oestrogen tended to have pear-shaped bodies and \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov\u002Fpubmed\u002F3224970\"\u003Emore subcutaneous fat\u003C\u002Fa\u003E, though not necessarily more fat overall.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECell swell\u003Cbr \u002F\u003E\u003C\u002Fstrong\u003E\u003Cbr \u002F\u003EFinally, there&rsquo;s the top menace of many women on the pill: bloating.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThat icky, swollen feeling happens because oestrogen also affects the way the body metabolises water, by influencing \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov\u002Fpmc\u002Farticles\u002FPMC2849969\u002F\"\u003Ethe production of certain proteins in the kidneys\u003C\u002Fa\u003E. The end result is that the body retains more fluid than it usually would. This then seeps into fat cells, causing them to swell up. Because women tend to store more fat in their breasts, hips and thighs, these areas can expand the most.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E"},"cardType":"Body","iFrameType":"","id":"future\u002Farticle\u002F20181003-does-the-birth-control-pill-make-you-fat-14"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[]},"cardType":"Image","iFrameType":"","image":["p06mvlb2"],"imageAlignment":"centre","id":"future\u002Farticle\u002F20181003-does-the-birth-control-pill-make-you-fat-15"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[]},"cardType":"PullQuote","iFrameType":"","pullQuote":"Synthetic oestrogen is six to 10 times more potent than the natural kind","id":"future\u002Farticle\u002F20181003-does-the-birth-control-pill-make-you-fat-16"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[],"html":"\u003Cp\u003EThis also happens on a smaller scale in women who aren&rsquo;t on the pill, \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fen.wikipedia.org\u002Fwiki\u002FPremenstrual_water_retention\"\u003Eduring the week just before their period\u003C\u002Fa\u003E. But it&rsquo;s exaggerated by the contraceptive because \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov\u002Fpmc\u002Farticles\u002FPMC2849969\u002F\"\u003Esynthetic oestrogen is six to 10 times more potent than the natural kind\u003C\u002Fa\u003E, and because it&rsquo;s taken nearly every day, which means the levels of both hormones are more constant.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003ESo while the pill may not be leading to long-term weight gain, some women could still find that their clothes fit differently.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003EFluid retention may also help to explain why some women report that the pill increases their cup size. There have been very few studies into the effect &ndash; understandably, most research tends to focus on breast cancer rather than size &ndash; but back in the 1990s a couple of Swedish scientists decided to take a look.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe contraceptive pill is known to increase a woman&rsquo;s risk of developing breast cancer slightly, both while she&rsquo;s taking it and in the 10 years afterwards. The researchers wanted to know \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Facademic.oup.com\u002Faje\u002Farticle\u002F145\u002F7\u002F571\u002F94585\"\u003Ewhether this might be because these women have larger breasts\u003C\u002Fa\u003E; there&rsquo;s an inherent risk in having (or growing) more cells, which is one reason tall people tend to be \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.theguardian.com\u002Fsociety\u002F2015\u002Foct\u002F01\u002Ftaller-people-more-likely-to-get-cancer-say-researchers\"\u003Emore susceptible to cancer\u003C\u002Fa\u003E.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003ETo find out, the team tracked the monthly cycles of 65 healthy women who either were on the pill, used to take it, or had never taken it. They found that not only did pill users have significantly larger breasts overall, but they were especially large at certain times of the month. Women who had previously been on the pill had an average-sized bust.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E"},"cardType":"Body","iFrameType":"","id":"future\u002Farticle\u002F20181003-does-the-birth-control-pill-make-you-fat-17"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[]},"cardType":"Image","iFrameType":"","image":["p06mvlp8"],"imageAlignment":"centre","id":"future\u002Farticle\u002F20181003-does-the-birth-control-pill-make-you-fat-18"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[],"html":"\u003Cp\u003EThe team didn&rsquo;t check the women&rsquo;s chest measurements before they started taking the pill, so it could be argued that these women had always had larger breasts. However, it seems likely this was due to the contraceptive pill, because their breast sizes weren&rsquo;t linked to the normal factors you&rsquo;d expect &ndash; such as their height, BMI, or body weight &ndash; as in the women who weren&rsquo;t on the pill.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E"},"cardType":"Body","iFrameType":"","id":"future\u002Farticle\u002F20181003-does-the-birth-control-pill-make-you-fat-19"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[]},"cardType":"PullQuote","iFrameType":"","pullQuote":"The hormones in the pill are actually causing women&rsquo;s breasts to grow","id":"future\u002Farticle\u002F20181003-does-the-birth-control-pill-make-you-fat-20"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[],"html":"\u003Cp\u003EExactly how this happens remains a mystery. The breast expansion could just be swelling from fluid retention, but another possibility is that the hormones in the pill are actually causing women&rsquo;s breasts to grow. For example, the burst of growth that happens each month, and is necessary to maintain a constant size, could be lasting a bit longer. This would lead to more tissue overall &ndash; and explain the heightened cancer risk.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOf course, whatever subtle effects the pill has on your figure &ndash; for better or for worse &ndash; millions of women feel that it&rsquo;s worth it. \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.reddit.com\u002Fr\u002Ffatlogic\u002Fcomments\u002F2p9wxr\u002Fbirth_control_made_me_gain_125lbs_and_make_women\u002F\"\u003EAs one Reddit user put it\u003C\u002Fa\u003E, no birth control at all is likely to lead to 25 to 35 pounds (11-15kg) of weight gain over the course of nine months.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cem\u003EThis story is part of the \u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Ca href=\"http:\u002F\u002Fbbc.com\u002Ffuture\u002Fstory\u002F20180521-the-health-gap-how-women-experience-the-medical-system\" target=\"_blank\"\u003EHealth Gap\u003C\u002Fa\u003E,\u003C\u002Fstrong\u003E a special series about how men and women experience the medical system &ndash; and their own health &ndash; in starkly different ways.\u003C\u002Fem\u003E\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cem\u003EDo you have an experience to share? Or are you just interested in sharing information about women's health and wellbeing? Join our Facebook group\u003Cstrong\u003E \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fbbc.in\u002F2LQHVAC\" target=\"_blank\"\u003EFuture Woman\u003C\u002Fa\u003E \u003C\u002Fstrong\u003Eand be a part of the conversation about the day-to-day issues that affect women&rsquo;s lives.&nbsp;\u003C\u002Fem\u003E\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cem\u003EJoin 800,000+ Future fans by liking us on&nbsp;\u003C\u002Fem\u003E\u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.facebook.com\u002FBBCFuture\" target=\"_blank\"\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cem\u003EFacebook\u003C\u002Fem\u003E\u003C\u002Fstrong\u003E\u003C\u002Fa\u003E\u003Cem\u003E, or follow us on&nbsp;\u003C\u002Fem\u003E\u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Ftwitter.com\u002Fbbc_future\" target=\"_blank\"\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cem\u003ETwitter\u003C\u002Fem\u003E\u003C\u002Fstrong\u003E\u003C\u002Fa\u003E\u003Cem\u003E.\u003C\u002Fem\u003E\u003C\u002Fp\u003E"},"cardType":"Body","iFrameType":"","id":"future\u002Farticle\u002F20181003-does-the-birth-control-pill-make-you-fat-21"}],"collection":["future\u002Fcolumn\u002Fhealth-gap"],"disableAdverts":false,"displayDate":"2018-10-04T01:00:00Z","embeddedCustomHtml":"","embeddedInfographicUrl":"","embeddedType":"","geolocation":null,"headlineLong":"How the pill changes your body 